<p>Installation itself usually takes 1-2 days for residential systems, followed by city inspection and SCE interconnection approval. The city inspection covers electrical connections, grounding, and structural attachments, while SCE's Permission to Operate (PTO) authorizes your system to begin generating credits. Most Long Beach installations are completed on composition shingle or tile roofs, though ground-mount systems are popular for larger properties in areas like Bixby Knolls and Los Cerritos.</p>

